  "title": "ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><p>• Provide administrative and document control support to the General Contractor’s project team</p><p>• Manage project documents and drawings, including filing, version control, and distribution</p><p>• Coordinate project correspondence with clients, consultants, and subcontractors</p><p>• Track submissions, RFIs, and approvals, and follow up for timely close-out</p><p>• Assist in preparation and tracking of progress claims and payment documents</p><p>• Maintain SharePoint or internal document management systems and manage access permissions</p><p>• Circulate documents internally for review and approval, and support meeting coordination</p><p>• Perform any other ad-hoc duties as assigned</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>• Minimum 3 years of construction industry experience</p><p>• Positive, proactive, detail-oriented, and responsible attitude</p><p>• Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</p><p>• Good communication, reading, and writing skills in English and Chinese to liaise with Chinese-speaking associates</p>",
